column5: # Global mean sea level (in meters) is estimated from the Rahmstorf 2007 model with Markov Chain Monte Carlo.
# This method assumes AR1 autocorrelation and heteroskedatic observation errors.
#  Sea-level is projected into the future with RCP 8.5 scenario temperatures and the best estimated parameters from the MCMC analysis.
# Temperature anomalies are with respect to the 20th century average. Historic temperatures from 1880 to 2013 are from NOAA.
# The RCP 8.5 temperatures are from 2014 to 2300 and are collected from the CNRM-CM5 model.
